95
00:04:09,650 --> 00:04:11,351
'What's the caloric reflex?'

96
00:04:11,384 --> 00:04:12,953
Slow deviation to the stimulus.

97
00:04:12,986 --> 00:04:14,621
And then?

98
00:04:14,655 --> 00:04:15,656
Uh..

99
00:04:15,689 --> 00:04:17,624
Saccadic return to the midline.

100
00:04:17,658 --> 00:04:20,827
Date of birth, 9/12/73.

101
00:04:20,861 --> 00:04:22,663
Dr. Benton ever in a good mood?

102
00:04:22,696 --> 00:04:25,065
He has his moments.

103
00:04:25,098 --> 00:04:27,367
'Go ahead.'

104
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:28,434
'No response.'

105
00:04:28,468 --> 00:04:30,370
Looks like she's a donor.

106
00:04:30,403 --> 00:04:32,372
I'll be right back.

107
00:04:32,405 --> 00:04:34,474
Is there any other family
we can call for you?

108
00:04:34,508 --> 00:04:36,042
Her‐her parents live
in Minnesota.

109
00:04:36,076 --> 00:04:38,645
We were, we're gonna
drive there today.

110
00:04:38,679 --> 00:04:41,347
‐ This is Dr. Corday.
‐ I'm so sorry, Mr. Pruitt.

111
00:04:42,583 --> 00:04:44,551
Are you gonna operate?

112
00:04:44,585 --> 00:04:46,019
The bullet passed
through the brain stem.

113
00:04:46,052 --> 00:04:48,488
I'm afraid no surgery
can repair that.

114
00:04:49,990 --> 00:04:50,924
Well..

115
00:04:52,893 --> 00:04:56,362
...is there any chance
that she'll s‐survive?

116
00:04:56,396 --> 00:04:58,298
She's no longer breathing
on her own.

117
00:05:00,100 --> 00:05:03,003
We have to wait and see
if she regains consciousness.

118
00:05:03,036 --> 00:05:05,606
But it's highly unlikely.

119
00:05:05,639 --> 00:05:07,941
The medical exam is consistent
with brain death.

120
00:05:11,978 --> 00:05:14,347
I was still asleep
when she left.

121
00:05:17,618 --> 00:05:20,787
I know this is a difficult time,
but we found a donor card.

122
00:05:20,821 --> 00:05:22,623
