123
00:05:22,656 --> 00:05:25,425
Your wife wanted
to be an organ donor.

124
00:05:25,458 --> 00:05:28,094
Oh, yeah, I‐I guess
that's what she wanted to..

125
00:05:28,128 --> 00:05:29,930
‐ Can I go see her?
‐ Yeah, sure.

126
00:05:31,765 --> 00:05:33,466
Elizabeth, we need you in here.

127
00:05:36,002 --> 00:05:37,971
Started an 18 gage
in the left AC.

128
00:05:38,004 --> 00:05:42,042
Rudy Escalona, 15 years old,
LOC from blunt head trauma.

129
00:05:42,075 --> 00:05:44,978
One, two, three.

130
00:05:45,011 --> 00:05:47,047
'Boxing league. He took a lot
of punches during practice.'

131
00:05:47,080 --> 00:05:48,782
Any medical problems, Rudy?

132
00:05:48,815 --> 00:05:50,617
Huh?

133
00:05:50,651 --> 00:05:51,985
No, my son's in good shape.

134
00:05:52,018 --> 00:05:53,587
Do you know where you are?

135
00:05:53,620 --> 00:05:54,855
I hit him, man.

136
00:05:54,888 --> 00:05:56,022
I hit him good.

137
00:05:56,056 --> 00:05:57,991
Pulse ox is 98
on two liters.

138
00:05:58,024 --> 00:05:59,492
Pupils equal and reactive.

139
00:05:59,526 --> 00:06:01,027
Do you know what year it is?

140
00:06:01,061 --> 00:06:02,462
Nobody thought I could do it.

141
00:06:03,496 --> 00:06:04,598
Answer the doctor.

142
00:06:04,631 --> 00:06:05,832
But I did it.

143
00:06:05,866 --> 00:06:07,801
Squeeze my hand, Rudy.

144
00:06:07,834 --> 00:06:09,936
‐ Haleh?
‐ He's not responding.

145
00:06:09,970 --> 00:06:12,573
We need to get some information
from you, sir.

146
00:06:12,606 --> 00:06:14,040
Airway's okay.
Still has a gag.

147
00:06:14,074 --> 00:06:15,141
No, I‐I'll stay.

148
00:06:15,175 --> 00:06:16,176
Uh, after the X‐rays

149
00:06:16,209 --> 00:06:17,544
you can come back.

150
00:06:17,578 --> 00:06:19,580
Abdomen soft,
no guarding or rebounds.

151
00:06:21,682 --> 00:06:24,417
‐ How late are you on?
‐ Peter should be back by 6:00.

152
00:06:24,450 --> 00:06:27,053
I'm on till 10:00.
Can you check Rachel's homework?

153
00:06:27,087 --> 00:06:29,590
Sure. Lateral C‐spine
and a head CT.

154
00:06:29,623 --> 00:06:31,491
She needs help
with her trinomials.

155
00:06:31,525 --> 00:06:32,859
Normal Babinski.

156
00:06:32,893 --> 00:06:34,427
I believe
I failed algebra.

157
00:06:34,460 --> 00:06:36,597
It's either that
or the Revolutionary War.

158
00:06:36,630 --> 00:06:38,532
I'll stick with math.

159
00:06:38,565 --> 00:06:39,933
Why can't you talk
to Human Resources?

160
00:06:39,966 --> 00:06:41,502
It won't change the outcome.

161
00:06:41,535 --> 00:06:42,536
Nicole's had a tough time.

162
00:06:42,569 --> 00:06:43,737
She deserves a second chance.

163
00:06:43,770 --> 00:06:45,105
Is that your objective opinion?

164
00:06:45,138 --> 00:06:46,540
Okay, she made a mistake

165
00:06:46,573 --> 00:06:47,774
but I know it won't
happen again.

166
00:06:47,808 --> 00:06:49,510
Look, the‐the hospital
has a zero‐tolerance

167
00:06:49,543 --> 00:06:50,944
policy against stealing.

168
00:06:50,977 --> 00:06:52,779
But, if you explain
the circumstances

169
00:06:52,813 --> 00:06:53,814
