170
00:06:53,847 --> 00:06:55,516
There is nothing
to explain.

171
00:06:55,549 --> 00:06:56,950
Kerry, just do it
as favor to me.

172
00:06:56,983 --> 00:06:58,051
I'm sorry, I can't.

173
00:06:58,084 --> 00:06:59,553
Or you won't?

174
00:06:59,586 --> 00:07:01,454
Please, I got her the job.

175
00:07:01,487 --> 00:07:03,724
You should have screened
her first.

176
00:07:03,757 --> 00:07:05,726
Carter, what is this abscess
still doing in exam four?

177
00:07:05,759 --> 00:07:06,960
It's peri‐rectal.

178
00:07:06,993 --> 00:07:08,094
Yeah, it definitely
needs surgery.

179
00:07:08,128 --> 00:07:10,063
So, you're on this too, Susan?

180
00:07:10,096 --> 00:07:11,231
Carter wanted
a second opinion.

181
00:07:11,264 --> 00:07:13,233
No. Call Surgery, we're busy.

182
00:07:13,266 --> 00:07:15,035
One doctor per patient.

183
00:07:16,937 --> 00:07:18,572
Have fun suturing.

184
00:07:18,605 --> 00:07:20,507
Have fun
with your rectum.

185
00:07:20,541 --> 00:07:23,109
When was your last tetanus shot?

186
00:07:23,143 --> 00:07:26,179
Uh, you better ask my dad, I..

187
00:07:26,212 --> 00:07:27,781
Jorge, this is Dr. Lewis.

188
00:07:27,814 --> 00:07:29,983
Hi. How's his exam?

189
00:07:30,016 --> 00:07:32,519
Uh, two centimeter lac
on the labial mucosa.

190
00:07:32,553 --> 00:07:35,689
I'd suggest an interrupted
4.0 vicryl.

191
00:07:35,722 --> 00:07:36,957
‐ How did you get hurt?
‐ Ow.

192
00:07:36,990 --> 00:07:38,692
He‐he was boxing.

193
00:07:38,725 --> 00:07:41,061
‐ And the other guy?
‐ You tell me.

194
00:07:41,094 --> 00:07:44,097
The other patient in trauma one.
Jorge's little brother, Rudy.

195
00:07:44,130 --> 00:07:46,900
Yeah, he got in a good one,
I kind of lost it

196
00:07:46,933 --> 00:07:49,503
but I didn't mean to hurt him.
Not bad.

197
00:07:49,536 --> 00:07:51,204
There you are.

198
00:07:51,237 --> 00:07:53,740
‐ How's Rudy?
‐ They say he's gonna wake up.

199
00:07:53,774 --> 00:07:55,909
He's gonna be alright.
You okay?

200
00:07:55,942 --> 00:07:57,678
He needs a couple
of stitches.

201
00:07:57,711 --> 00:07:59,980
‐ Does it hurt?
‐ No.

202
00:08:00,013 --> 00:08:01,648
This is one tough kid.

203
00:08:04,217 --> 00:08:06,687
Be careful of your reaction
to the testimony.

204
00:08:06,720 --> 00:08:08,154
No sighing, no faces.

205
00:08:08,188 --> 00:08:09,222
What if I need
to ask you a question?

206
00:08:09,255 --> 00:08:10,824
Write it down,
I'll address it.

207
00:08:10,857 --> 00:08:12,092
Schedule change,
they switched judges on us.

208
00:08:12,125 --> 00:08:13,527
‐ Who did we draft?
‐ Alter.

209
00:08:13,560 --> 00:08:14,761
Is that good or bad?

210
00:08:14,795 --> 00:08:15,996
Well, he always favors
the mother.

211
00:08:16,029 --> 00:08:17,831
It's not a problem
in this case.

212
00:08:17,864 --> 00:08:19,700
Even though it wouldn't hurt
to show your maternal side.

213
00:08:19,733 --> 00:08:21,034
‐ Right.
‐ That the tie you're wearing?

214
00:08:21,067 --> 00:08:22,603
Mm, what's wrong with it?

215
00:08:22,636 --> 00:08:23,670
Well, it's a little showy,
don't you think?

216
00:08:25,739 --> 00:08:28,041
And when it comes your turn,
don't get too emotional.

217
00:08:28,074 --> 00:08:30,744
You don't wanna come across
as cold or unfeeling either.

218
00:08:30,777 --> 00:08:32,679
You make it sound like
it's some kind of performance.

219
00:08:32,713 --> 00:08:33,780
Well, it is.

220
00:08:35,115 --> 00:08:36,717
That is the whitest tie
I've ever seen.

221
00:08:37,684 --> 00:08:39,319
It's blue.

222
00:08:39,352 --> 00:08:41,688
She's breaking out in hives.
It's like an allergic reaction.

223
00:08:41,722 --> 00:08:42,723
‐ To what?
‐ I don't know.

224
00:08:42,756 --> 00:08:43,957
Nobody's figured it out.

225
00:08:43,990 --> 00:08:45,325
We've been to three ERs
this week.

226
00:08:45,358 --> 00:08:46,727
Fifty of Benadryl
in the field.

227
00:08:46,760 --> 00:08:47,928
Push 125 of Solu‐Medrol.

228
00:08:47,961 --> 00:08:49,763
We've found guided
imagery helps.

229
00:08:49,796 --> 00:08:50,997
Close your eyes, honey.

230
00:08:51,031 --> 00:08:52,198
Who's your doctor?

231
00:08:52,232 --> 00:08:53,233
Oh, he's in Syracuse.

232
00:08:53,266 --> 00:08:54,601
'We're on our honeymoon.'

233
00:08:54,635 --> 00:08:55,969
'Go to your peaceful place..'

234
00:08:59,339 --> 00:09:01,341
Oh, better hide
the good silver.

235
00:09:01,374 --> 00:09:02,576
What's she doing here?

236
00:09:02,609 --> 00:09:04,110
Meeting with personnel.

237
00:09:04,144 --> 00:09:06,312
I heard
she's getting fired.

238
00:09:06,346 --> 00:09:09,716
Let our souls intermingle.

239
00:09:09,750 --> 00:09:11,818
Uh, any new soaps or pesticides?

240
00:09:11,852 --> 00:09:13,219
Everything's the same.

241
00:09:13,253 --> 00:09:15,221
‐ What about latex?
‐ What do you mean?

242
00:09:15,255 --> 00:09:17,257
Yeah, some people are allergic
to, uh, rubber gloves

243
00:09:17,290 --> 00:09:18,592
tennis shoes, condoms..

244
00:09:18,625 --> 00:09:20,026
‐ Condoms?
‐ We stopped using them.

245
00:09:20,060 --> 00:09:21,327
‐ 'When?'
‐ A couple weeks ago.

246
00:09:21,361 --> 00:09:23,063
We're trying to get pregnant.

247
00:09:23,096 --> 00:09:25,098
Everything's alright.
Feel the warmth of the sun.

248
00:09:25,131 --> 00:09:27,968
Just embrace the joy.

249
00:09:28,001 --> 00:09:30,737
Rudy's vital signs
and oxygen level are good.

250
00:09:30,771 --> 00:09:33,206
‐ Is he awake now?
‐ Uh, not quite yet.

251
00:09:33,239 --> 00:09:35,108
But he might be able
to hear you.

252
00:09:35,141 --> 00:09:36,910
‐ Go ahead.
‐ Thanks.

253
00:09:41,247 --> 00:09:44,117
'Even before I married Carla,
we discussed it.'

254
00:09:44,150 --> 00:09:46,319
I knew it would be
a challenge but..

255
00:09:46,352 --> 00:09:47,888
...we agreed
that our first priority

256
